 Stimulus Sensitivity
Threat Sensitivity — How prone the villager is to perceive danger

Sound Sensitivity — Reaction to loud noises (explosions, thunder, etc.)

Visual Sensitivity — Response to things seen (e.g. fighting, death, zombies)

Crowd Influence Bias — How easily they're influenced by the surrounding mob behavior

Pattern Recognition — How well they connect past events to current stimuli

Alertness — Overall awareness of surroundings and capacity to detect change

Information Spread Rate — Speed at which they choose to spread news

Information Trust Bias — Likelihood of believing heard/gossiped info

Empathy Trigger — Tendency to mirror or emotionally sync with others nearby

🔸 Internal Response Modifiers
Fear Amplification — How fear scales with proximity/severity of stimulus

Curiosity Trigger — If an event draws attention instead of scaring them

Panic Threshold — How intense a stimulus must be before causing panic

Aggression Trigger — Proneness to respond with hostility

Empathy Overload — If emotional input from too many sources breaks composure

Grief Response — Tendency to react emotionally to death/loss

Excitement Threshold — How easily positive stimuli cause joy/interest

Social Reinforcement Bias — Will they go along with crowd consensus or stay individual

Shock Absorption — How quickly they return to baseline after a stimulus

Communication Reflex — How likely they are to spread emotional response




